quran[24]{c,v,t}:
  18,75,"He Said: \"Did I not say to you, that you will never/not be able (to have) patience with me"
  18,76,"He said: \"If I asked/questioned you , about a thing after it, so do not accompany/befriend me, you had reached an excuse from at me"
  18,77,"So they (B) left/set out until when they (B) came (to) a village/urban city, they asked its people to be fed, so they refused/hated that they have them (B) as guests/help them , so they (B) found in it a wall wanting that to fall down/be wrecked, so he raised it, he (Moses) said: \"If you wanted/willed you would have taken/received on (for) it a wage/fee"
  18,78,"He said: \"This (is) separation between me and between you, I will inform you with (an) explanation/interpretation on (of) what you were not able (to have) patience on it"
  18,79,"As for the ship/boat, so it was to (owned by) poorest of poor/poor oppressed working in the sea/ocean/river , so I wanted that I defect it , and behind them was a king he takes/receives every ship/boat forcefully/unjustly/violently"
  18,80,"And as for the boy/servant , so his parents were believing, so We feared that he burdens/oppresses them (with) tyranny/arrogance and disbelief"
  18,81,So We wanted/intended that their (B)`s Lord exchanges/substitutes (for) them (B) better than him and purification/correction and nearer/closer (in) mercy/relation
  18,82,"And as for the wall, so it was (belonging) to two boys , two orphans in the city/town, and under it was a treasure/buried treasure for them (B), and their (B)`s father was correct/righteous, so your Lord wanted/willed that they (B) reach their (B)`s maturity/strength, and they (B) bring out their (B)`s treasure/buried treasure, mercy from your Lord, and I did not make/do it from my matter/affair, that (is) explanation/interpretation (of) what you were not able (to have) patience on it"
  18,83,"And they ask/question you about (owner) of the two horns/powers/glories , Say: \"I will read/recite on (to) you from him a reminder/remembrance"
  18,84,"We have highly positioned/strengthened for him in the earth/Planet Earth, and We gave/brought him from every thing a reason/motive/connection"
  18,85,So he followed a reason/motive/connection
  18,86,"Until when he reached the sun`s sunset/west , he found it departing/declining (setting) in (at a) water well/spring mixed with black (foul) mud, and he found at it a nation, We said: \"You (owner) of the two horns/powers/glories, either that you torture, and either you take in them a goodness/beauty"
  18,87,"He said: \"As for who caused injustice/oppression, so we will/shall torture him, then he be returned to his Lord, so He tortures him an awful/obscene/severe torture"
  18,88,"And as for who believed and made/did correct/righteous deeds, so to him the best`s/goodnesses` reward/reimbursement , and we will say to him from our order/matter ease/flexibility"
  18,89,Then he followed a reason/motive/connection
  18,90,"Until when he reached the sun`s place and time of appearance/ascent , he found it appears/ascends/rises on a nation We did not make/put from other than it a cover/protection/shelter"
  18,91,"Like that, and We had comprehended/enveloped with what (is) at/near him (with) knowledge"
  18,92,Then he followed a reason/motive/connection
  18,93,"Until when he reached between the two barriers/obstacles/mountains , he found from other than them (B) a nation they are not about to/almost understand a saying/opinion and belief"
  18,94,"They said: \"You (owner) of the two horns/powers/glories, that Yagog and Magog (are) corrupting in the earth/Planet Earth, so do we make/put for you (a) royalty/retainer/expense/tribute on that you put/create between us and between them a barrier/obstacle"
  18,95,"He said: \"What my Lord highly positioned/strengthened/empowered me in it (is) best , so help/support me with power/strength , I make/create/put between you and between them a blockage/barrier"
  18,96,"Give/bring me the huge pieces of iron. Until when he straightened/leveled/equalized between the two sides/directions/mountain sides , he said: \"Blow.\" Until when he made it a fire, he said: \"Give/bring me, I pour on it molten copper/brass/iron"
  18,97,"So they did not rise/diffuse/spread over (it, nor) that they mount/ascend it , and they were not able (of) piercing/penetration for it"
  18,98,"He said: \"That (is) mercy from my Lord, so if my Lord`s promise came, he made it flattened/leveled off and my Lord`s promise was truthfully (truthful)"